text-sm leading-relaxed my-2","children":["That's what our auditor told us six months ago when we first attempted SOC 2 certification. The problem? Traditional SOC 2 frameworks weren't designed for systems that make real-time decisions without human oversight."]}],["$","br","6",{}],["$","p","7",{"className":"text-slate-300 text-sm leading-relaxed my-2","children":["Fast-forward to today: Vienna OS has become the first AI agent governance platform to achieve SOC 2 Type I compliance. Here's what we learned."]}],["$","br","8",{}],["$","h2","9",{"className":"text-xl font-bold text-white mt-10 mb-4","children":"Where Traditional SOC 2 Falls Short"}],["$","br","10",{}],["$","p","11",{"className":"text-slate-400 italic text-sm mt-6","children":"*Problem 1: Decision Speed vs. Human Oversight*"}],["$","p","12",{"className":"text-slate-300 text-sm leading-relaxed my-2","children":["Traditional controls assume human involvement in critical decisions. AI agents can execute thousands of actions per second."]}],["$","br","13",{}],["$","p","14",{"className":"text-slate-400 italic text-sm mt-6","children":"*Problem 2: Dynamic Risk Assessment*"}],["$","p","15",{"className":"text-slate-300 text-sm leading-relaxed my-2","children":["Standard security controls are binary: allowed or blocked. AI agents need risk-aware controls."]}],["$","br","16",{}],["$","p","17",{"className":"text-slate-400 italic text-sm mt-6","children":"*Problem 3: Audit Trail Complexity*"}],["$","p","18",{"className":"text-slate-300 text-sm leading-relaxed my-2","children":["AI agents make complex decisions requiring audit trails that capture intent, reasoning, and risk evaluation."]}],["$","br","19",{}],["$","h2","20",{"className":"text-xl font-bold text-white mt-10 mb-4","children":"Trust Services Criteria for AI Agents"}],["$","br","21",{}],["$","h3","22",{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white mt-8 mb-3","children":"Security: Protecting Against Unauthorized Access"}],["$","p","23",{"className":"text-slate-400 italic text-sm mt-6","children":"*What Auditors Want:*"}],["$","li","24",{"className":"text-slate-300 ml-4 text-sm","children":"Cryptographic authentication of AI agent identities"}],["$","li","25",{"className":"text-slate-300 ml-4 text-sm","children":"Scoped permissions that limit blast radius"}],["$","li","26",{"className":"text-slate-300 ml-4 text-sm","children":"Real-time monitoring of agent behavior"}],["$","li","27",{"className":"text-slate-300 ml-4 text-sm","children":"Secure credential management"}],["$","br","28",{}],["$","p","29",{"className":"text-slate-400 italic text-sm mt-6","children":"*Vienna OS Implementation:*"}],["$","li","30",{"className":"text-slate-300 ml-4 text-sm","children":"Every agent action requires cryptographic warrant"}],["$","li","31",{"className":"text-slate-300 ml-4 text-sm","children":"Risk-tiered permission system (T0-T3)"}],["$","li","32",{"className":"text-slate-300 ml-4 text-sm","children":"Continuous behavioral monitoring"}],["$","li","33",{"className":"text-slate-300 ml-4 text-sm","children":"Zero-trust credential architecture"}],["$","br","34",{}],["$","h3","35",{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white mt-8 mb-3","children":"Availability: System Operation and Accessibility"}],["$","p","36",{"className":"text-slate-400 italic text-sm mt-6","children":"*What Auditors Want:*"}],["$","li","37",{"className":"text-slate-300 ml-4 text-sm","children":"Defined uptime requirements for AI governance"}],["$","li","38",{"className":"text-slate-300 ml-4 text-sm","children":"Monitoring of AI system performance"}],["$","li","39",{"className":"text-slate-300 ml-4 text-sm","children":"Incident response procedures for AI failures"}],["$","br","40",{}],["$","h3","41",{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white mt-8 mb-3","children":"Processing Integrity: Complete, Valid, Accurate Processing"}],["$","p","42",{"className":"text-slate-400 italic text-sm mt-6","children":"*What Auditors Want:*"}],["$","li","43",{"className":"text-slate-300 ml-4 text-sm","children":"Verification that AI agents do exactly what they're authorized to do"}],["$","li","44",{"className":"text-slate-300 ml-4 text-sm","children":"Controls preventing unauthorized modifications"}],["$","li","45",{"className":"text-slate-300 ml-4 text-sm","children":"Data validation at input and output"}],["$","br","46",{}],["$","h3","47",{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white mt-8 mb-3","children":"Confidentiality: Protection of Sensitive Information"}],["$","p","48",{"className":"text-slate-400 italic text-sm mt-6","children":"*What Auditors Want:*"}],["$","li","49",{"className":"text-slate-300 ml-4 text-sm","children":"Data classification for AI training and inference"}],["$","li","50",{"className":"text-slate-300 ml-4 text-sm","children":"Controls preventing data leakage between tenants"}],["$","li","51",{"className":"text-slate-300 ml-4 text-sm","children":"Encryption of AI model weights and training data"}],["$","br","52",{}],["$","h3","53",{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white mt-8 mb-3","children":"Privacy: Collection, Use, and Disposal of Personal Information"}],["$","p","54",{"className":"text-slate-400 italic text-sm mt-6","children":"*What Auditors Want:*"}],["$","li","55",{"className":"text-slate-300 ml-4 text-sm","children":"Privacy controls for AI systems processing personal data"}],["$","li","56",{"className":"text-slate-300 ml-4 text-sm","children":"Data retention policies for AI-generated insights"}],["$","li","57",{"className":"text-slate-300 ml-4 text-sm","children":"User consent mechanisms for AI processing"}],["$","br","58",{}],["$","h2","59",{"className":"text-xl font-bold text-white mt-10 mb-4","children":"The Audit Evidence That Actually Works"}],["$","br","60",{}],["$","h3","61",{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white mt-8 mb-3","children":"1. Warrant-Based Audit Trails"}],["$","p","62",{"className":"text-slate-300 text-sm leading-relaxed my-2","children":["Instead of hoping agents behave,